text: Macon County is a county in the U.S. state of Alabama. In 2020, 19,532 people lived there. The county seat is Tuskegee. The name is in honor of Nathaniel Macon, a member of the United States Senate from North Carolina. Macon County was founded on December 18, 1832. ==References== Category:Alabama counties Category:1832 establishments in Alabama
title: Macon County, Alabama
